                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d511">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/14951</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Chinese Embassy</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="5" xml:id="d511fn5">Read as an oral statement and handed to the Chinese
                        Ambassador on May 1 by the Adviser on Political Relations.</note>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content" calendar="gregorian"
                        when="1939-05-01">undated</date>
                </dateline>
                <p>The Chinese Embassy’s <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi> of April 14 relating to
                    proposed principles of cooperation in the Far East has been read with care.</p>
                <pb facs="0538" n="534" xml:id="pg_534"/>
                <p>It is believed that the Chinese Embassy is fully aware of this Government’s
                    attitude on the subject of cooperation and parallel action. Clear indications of
                    this attitude are given in the texts of documents which have been released to
                    the press by the Department of State and by the White House.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
